---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Lotus Rose Counseling in Orem, UT | Our Story"
  description="Learn about Lotus Rose Counseling — a therapy practice in Orem, Utah founded by Joy Bouchard, LCSW, specializing in trauma, postpartum, grief, and EMDR therapy."
>

  <!-- Full-Bleed Hero -->
  <section class="hero-fullbleed">
    <div class="hero-fullbleed-bg">
      <img src="/florals/floral-contact.webp" alt="Dried flowers — Lotus Rose Counseling story" width="1920" height="1080" fetchpriority="high" />
    </div>
    <div class="hero-fullbleed-overlay"></div>
    <div class="hero-fullbleed-content">
      <p class="section-label">Our Story</p>
      <h1>Why "Lotus Rose"?</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Named for a woman who knew what it meant to bloom in hard ground.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Story Behind the Name (combines grandma origin + symbolism) -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-container">
        <p class="section-label">The Woman Behind the Name</p>
        <h2>Lotus Rose</h2>
        <p>The name reflects both a meaningful personal connection and the deeper symbolism behind the work of therapy. Lotus Rose Counseling is named for the founder's grandmother, Lotus Rose, a woman who rose through significant adversity.</p>
        <p>As a young mother, she cared for her family alone while her husband was away at war. Later, she faced the loss of her husband at a much younger age than anticipated, continuing on to navigate life on her own. Despite these challenges, she remained strong and compassionate, with a great sense of humor.</p>
        <p>Her life reflects the quiet resilience so many women carry. The ability to endure, adapt, and continue caring for those around them, even in the midst of their own hardship.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lotus-rose-gallery">
        <img src="/photos/about-3.webp" alt="Lotus Rose as a young woman with her husband" width="800" height="1067" loading="lazy" />
        <img src="/photos/about-2.webp" alt="Lotus Rose with her husband later in life" width="800" height="900" loading="lazy" />
        <img src="/photos/about-1.webp" alt="Lotus Rose smiling in her later years" width="800" height="900" loading="lazy" />
      </div>

      <div class="text-container symbolism-block">
        <h3>What the Lotus and Rose Represent</h3>
        <p>The lotus rises from muddy, uncertain waters to bloom into something whole and beautiful. The rose carries both petals and thorns: love and vulnerability alongside the strength and boundaries that healing requires. Together, they represent the balance of resilience and tenderness that sits at the heart of this work.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Joy's Story (split layout — portrait variant with framed photo) -->
  <div class="split-section split-section--portrait">
    <div class="split-inner">
      <div class="split-content">
        <p class="section-label">The Founder</p>
        <h2>Joy Bouchard, LCSW</h2>
        <p>Joy founded Lotus Rose because she's lived the struggle. As a mother of three, she has her own journey with birth trauma, postpartum depression, and postpartum anxiety, with each child bringing a different experience.</p>
        <p>She knows what it's like to be searching for someone you can talk to, someone who can give guidance through the hardest chapters of motherhood. That's the practice she set out to build.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="split-image">
        <img src="/photos/joy-bouchard.webp" alt="Joy Bouchard, LCSW — founder of Lotus Rose Counseling" width="800" height="800" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Pull Quote -->
  <section class="bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-container">
        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p>"I wanted to create a place that was very safe, that felt warm and welcoming. All of our clinicians are trained in how to help specifically with women's issues. I wanted it to be a safe haven."</p>
          <cite>Joy Bouchard, LCSW — Founder</cite>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What We Do (combines What Makes Us Different + Who We Serve) -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-container">
        <p class="section-label">What We Do</p>
        <h2>Women's Mental Health Is Our Specialty</h2>
        <p>A lot of practices say they see women for postpartum or perinatal issues, but they also see everyone else for everything else. At Lotus Rose, women's mental health is our core focus. Every therapist is trained in trauma treatment, and every continuing education course is chosen specifically to get better at treating women's issues.</p>
        <p>We work with women navigating perinatal mental health, including postpartum depression, birth trauma, and infant loss, alongside childhood abuse recovery, grief, anxiety, depression, infertility, and the identity shifts that come with major life transitions. We also work with teens and children, especially those navigating grief, trauma, and behavioral challenges.</p>
        <p>Whatever brought you here, there's likely a therapist on our team with specific training for it. <a href="/services/">See the full list of services →</a></p>

        <div class="highlight-box">
          <h4>What We Believe</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>The therapeutic relationship is the foundation. You need to feel safe before you can heal.</li>
            <li>Therapy isn't just talking. There's training, technique, and expertise behind every session.</li>
            <li>Healing takes time. Most clients work with us for 6-12 months, and that's normal.</li>
            <li>There's room for humor in hard work. The space needs to feel human.</li>
            <li>You should never feel locked in. No contracts, no pressure, find the right fit.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Our Space -->
  <section class="bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-container text-center">
        <p class="section-label">Our Space</p>
        <h2>A Place That Feels Like Home</h2>
        <p>We've intentionally created a space that feels warm and inviting, with every detail thoughtfully designed to offer women a comfortable and welcoming environment.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="photo-grid" style="margin-top: 40px;">
        <img src="/photos/office-1.webp" alt="Therapy room at Lotus Rose Counseling in Orem, Utah" width="768" height="512" loading="lazy" />
        <img src="/photos/office-3.webp" alt="Warm therapy space at Lotus Rose Counseling" width="768" height="512" loading="lazy" />
        <img src="/photos/office-5.webp" alt="Lotus Rose Counseling office interior" width="768" height="512" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to Begin Your Healing Journey?</h2>
      <p>Schedule a free 15-minute consultation to find the right therapist for you.</p>
      <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content: center;">
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary">Schedule Free Consultation</a>
        <a href="tel:+18016424244" class="btn-secondary">Call (801) 642-4244</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .lotus-rose-gallery {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 48px auto 0;
  }
  .lotus-rose-gallery img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 360px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
  }
  .symbolism-block {
    margin-top: 56px;
    padding-top: 48px;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(61, 51, 48, 0.1);
  }

  /* Portrait variant — gives Joy's photo a contained, framed look
     instead of stretching edge to edge. Constrained to a centered
     max-width so text and image stay near each other on wide screens. */
  .split-section--portrait {
    background: var(--warm-cream);
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    min-height: auto;
    padding: 80px 0;
  }
  .split-section--portrait .split-inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr;
    gap: 60px;
    align-items: center;
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 40px;
  }
  .split-section--portrait .split-content {
    padding: 0;
  }
  .split-section--portrait .split-image {
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .split-section--portrait .split-image img {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 380px;
    height: auto;
    aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-medium);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .split-section--portrait { padding: 56px 0; }
    .split-section--portrait .split-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 32px;
      padding: 0 28px;
    }
    .split-section--portrait .split-image img {
      max-width: 320px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .lotus-rose-gallery { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 32px; }
    .lotus-rose-gallery img { height: 320px; }
    .symbolism-block { margin-top: 40px; padding-top: 32px; }
  }
</style>
